@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<section class="hero-panel">
    <span class="eyebrow">Week 7 Project 05</span>
    <h1>Build a local weather dashboard with mock data and automatic refresh.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This project simulates a weather service locally, then uses Fetch API and polling to keep the dashboard current without any external API.
    </p>
    <div class="action-row">
        <a class="button button-primary" asp-page="/Dashboard">Open The Weather Dashboard</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="/api/weatherdashboard" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View Raw JSON</a>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>What students practise</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Fetch local weather data from a mock API endpoint.</li>
            <li>Refresh dashboard panels manually and automatically.</li>
            <li>Use <code>setInterval()</code> for polling every 15 seconds.</li>
            <li>Handle loading states and message updates while data changes.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Why this stays beginner-friendly</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>No external weather API keys are required.</li>
            <li>All data changes come from a local simulation service.</li>
            <li>The same endpoint returns everything the dashboard needs.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="info-panel">
    <h2>Suggested walkthrough</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Load the dashboard and inspect the weather JSON response.</li>
        <li>Use the manual refresh button to compare the changing values.</li>
        <li>Wait 15 seconds and watch the dashboard update automatically.</li>
        <li>Stop the page and confirm the app still works fully offline.</li>
    </ol>
</section>
